A new project encouraging rooftop gardens in <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Chicago</ENAMEX> is bringing new meaning to the term `` urban jungle . ''
The roof of <ENAMEX TYPE="FAC">City Hall</ENAMEX> is being transformed into an urban oasis .
Rooftops normally absorb the hot sun and heat up the air in cities which can make pollution worse .
The project is part of a federal government study to see if rooftop gardens can have the opposite effect .
